3. cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence): The paper utilizes Metric Interval Temporal Logic (MITL) to specify high-level goals for the robot, which is a technique commonly used in artificial intelligence. 
4. cs.LG (Machine Learning): The paper utilizes Nonlinear Model Predictive Control (NMPC) methodology, which is a technique commonly used in machine learning. 
5. cs.SD (Software Development): While not the primary focus of the paper, the proposed framework for robot navigation may require software development to implement in practice.
